		<div class="mission_item text-center">
			<div class="mission_icon"><i class="fa fa-book" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
			<div class="mission_title">our story</div>
			<div class="mission_text">Founded as the first church in the community plan for Rancho Bernardo, our church
				has served the surrounding Poway, Escondido, 4S, Penasquitos and north San Diego neighborhoods for over
				50 years. We are a Presbyterian church in the PCUSA family of churches.</div>
		</div>

		<div class="mission_item text-center">
			<div class="mission_icon"><i class="fas fa-compass" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
			<div class="mission_title">our purpose</div>
			<div class="mission_text">Put simply, our church exists “For the glory of God alone.” The Latin, “Soli Deo
				gloria,” claimed by the church leaders as a centering belief, referenced by Johann Sebastian Bach on his
				musical pieces, is our starting point for our purpose and our beliefs.</div>
		</div>

		<div class="mission_item text-center">
			<div class="mission_icon"><i class="fas fa-sun" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
			<div class="mission_title">our future</div>
			<div class="mission_text">Our leadership of Elders and Pastoral staff focus on 3 to 4 key areas of our life
				together through which we might glorify God and faithfully steward our resources. Read details about
				this year’s focus on the Elders section of our Ministries page.</div>
		</div>

		<div class="mission_item text-center">
			<div class="mission_icon"><i class="fa fa-user" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
			<div class="mission_title">you</div>
			<div class="mission_text">Believers belong in a faith family - a place to join folks of all ages, grow in
				Christ, and bless the world. We offer you a chance to learn more about us and your place in God’s
				kingdom through a monthly dinner with the Senior Pastor. See the Events page for details.
			</div>
		</div>

	</div>
